race.description: The Victoria Hotel Port Fairy Cup Bm78 Handicap
race.comment: Tricky race. WILLMOTT (1) tackled a strong race at Bendigo first up and was solid before a smart win at Donald over 1350m, settling midfield and coming clear to score by two lengths. This is a touch harder but he can go on with it. FLYING MIKKI (4) kicked off this campaign at Murray Bridge and hit the line well over 1200m to grab third. He's run some very good races at 1400m and this is an ideal race. HEDONIST (6) is going well, far too good in easier company at Mt Gambier two back and measuring up well at Flemington latest. He's untested at 1400m but should handle it and measure up. HAY JOE (8) was beaten narrowly over this route when last seen and has minor claims in this tougher affair. JACKS ON ICE (2) is going okay and could give a sight with Meech on.
